Eating at Hometown is like watching and eating with the animals at the zoo. Their layout is such that there is no flow or control to the food lines. This means that you play bumper car dodgeball with all the other customers. They should have looked at Fresh Choice or some other buffet setup. Even 35 years ago my wife and I would go to Sir Georges in souther California and they did a better job with the layout. A better line setup would , I hope, help prevent the need to watchout for wild
